    <h2>Our Philosophy</h2>
    <p>
      Responsible breeding begins before a puppy is ever listed. We focus on
      planned care, steady handling, honest updates, and communication that helps
      families understand the breed and the commitment.
    </p>

    <p>
      We do not rush placements or treat approval as automatic. The goal is a
      prepared family, a well-supported puppy, and a relationship that remains
      positive after the puppy goes home.
    </p>

    <h2>Why Pekingese?</h2>
    <p>
      Pekingese are loyal, affectionate companions known for their strong bond
      with their families. Their dignified nature and gentle temperament can make
      them wonderful household companions when raised and placed responsibly.
    </p>

    <h2>Health, Care, and Disclosure</h2>
    <p>
      Puppy profiles may include age, gender, color, vaccination notes,
      veterinary status, registration details, and family-line information when
      available. Approved applicants can ask follow-up questions before taking
      next steps.
    </p>

    <div class="safety-panel">
      <h2>What Families Can Expect</h2>
      <ul class="trust-list">
        <li>Clear puppy availability labels such as Available, Reserved, or Sold.</li>
        <li>An application review before any invoice is created.</li>
        <li>A private tracking code for application status updates.</li>
        <li>Itemized adoption invoices only for approved buyers.</li>
      </ul>
    </div>

    <h2>Thoughtful Placement</h2>
    <p>
      Placing a puppy is a long-term commitment. Our adoption process exists to
      protect both the puppy and the adopting family. Applications are reviewed
      carefully, and placement decisions are made with the puppy's well-being as
      the top priority.
    </p>

    <p class="closing-note">
      Our goal is not simply to place puppies. It is to build lasting, positive
      relationships between our puppies and the families who welcome them.
    </p>
  </div>
